x4freetext: 1.911 MeV protons on metallic Li-7 layer of
6mm diam. on copper backing of 0.5 mm. Kinematically
collimated neutron beam forming a 120 degree cone.
Maximum neutron energy of 106 keV. Neutron scattering
on the Cu backing was neglected with uncertainty
The neutron spectrum is closely approximated (Fig.4)
to a Maxwellian shape with a temperature of 22-24 keV.
Measured relative neutron yield per energy interval
for 45, 30, 15, 0 deg of neutron emission angle is on
For neutron spectrum measurement. 90 cm distance
between neutron target and Li6 glass detector.
Except for Ba, natural metallic foils of 6mm diameter,
Thin samples in order to minimize scattering and
For monitor - metal Au of 112 mg/cm**2 thickness.
Effective thickness for Au-197 isotope 3.42E-04 at/b.
High resolution gamma-ray spectroscopy by Ge(Li)
Gamma intensity as function of time was measured.
Used to resolve the gamma spectra from the different
isotopes. In addition the half-life of the activated
nucleus was measured as a check.
Maxwellian averaged cross section measured directly
by fitting at thermal energy KT=22-24 keV.
cross section from kT=24 to 30 keV ( < 3.0%),
M.M. Dates were corrected for 4-digit year.
Free text was corrected to be "human-readable".
BIB information was added.Errors were added in COMMON.
Data points at 30 keV were moved in Subents 008-012.
EN was changed into KT in according to Table 3.
